benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles - Retrieve a bundle by external key

covered: Valid Request: Happy path covered (TC01) including status 200, JSON array response and Content-Type.
Query Parameters: Extensive coverage for externalKey, includedDeleted (TC02, TC06), audit enum (TC03–TC05), invalid/empty values (TC09, TC10, TC29), unsupported extra params (TC15).
Error Handling: Not-found and missing parameter cases covered (TC07, TC08, TC16).
Authorization: Unauthorized and forbidden scenarios included (TC11, TC12).
Service/Dependency Failures: Service/unavailable and dependency failure scenarios covered (TC13, TC28).
Security: Injection and XSS attempts are tested (TC19, TC20) and responses are expected not to leak sensitive errors.
Scalability & Performance: Response time (TC17), concurrency (TC18), large DB and large-number-of-bundles scenarios (TC27, TC14) are present.

Schema & Data Variants: Required fields and schema/backward-compatibility checks (TC30, TC22), non-ASCII keys (TC23), max/min length keys (TC24, TC25), and unexpected input formats (TC26) are covered.
gaps: Pagination: No tests exercise pagination parameters or validate paging behavior (page/offset/limit) or behavior when results span multiple pages.
Caching behavior / Conditional GET: No tests verify caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control), conditional GET semantics (If-None-Match / 304 responses) or validation of cache-related headers.
Rate limiting / Throttling: No tests simulate hitting rate limits or verify proper 429 handling and Retry-After headers.
Content negotiation and headers: Other response headers beyond Content-Type (e.g., Content-Length, charset) and Accept header behavior are not tested.
HTTP 500 / generic server error: There is coverage for dependency failure returning 503, but no explicit test for unexpected internal server error (500) and its safe error message handling.
Authentication token edge-cases: Tests do not cover expired tokens, token refresh flows, or token scope edge cases beyond basic 401/403.
Pagination-related performance: Large result tests exist but do not validate server-side paging performance or limits (e.g., max page size).
recommendations: Add pagination tests: include scenarios that request pages (limit/offset or page/size), validate total counts, boundary conditions (last page), and behavior when page params are out of range.
Add caching and conditional GET tests: verify ETag and Cache-Control headers, If-None-Match leading to 304, and correct cache headers for 200 responses.
Add rate-limiting tests: simulate many requests to exercise throttling rules, verify 429 responses and Retry-After header semantics.
Add content negotiation tests: send Accept headers (e.g., application/json, text/plain) and verify correct handling or rejection; assert other important response headers as required.
Add 500/internal-server-error tests: simulate an unexpected failure path that produces 500 and verify it does not leak sensitive information and follows error formatting conventions.
Add authentication edge-case tests: expired tokens, revoked tokens, and token scope/role variations to ensure proper 401/403 behavior beyond basic cases.
If pagination is implemented, include performance and correctness tests for very large result sets combined with paging parameters (ensure deterministic results).
